main event: A civilian in Baltimore, Maryland reported seeing a single object moving from south to northwest around 9:30 pm on May 10, 1964.
interesting points: The civilian called the airport to inquire about the object they had seen.
The National Space Agency responded to the civilian's inquiry, providing information about the passage of ECHO II, an artificial satellite, over Baltimore on June 30, 1964.
The USAF letter indicates that the civilian's observation was likely of the ECHO II satellite and not an unidentified flying object.
The report does not contain any photographs or physical evidence of the observed object.
The conclusion of the report is that the sighting had a possible conventional cause, identified as the ECHO II satellite.
result: possible conventional cause (identified as ECHO II satellite)
